***The Menu Bar***

-FILE
	|--> New File: Create a new blank interface file.  The initial contents
	|		of the file are designated by creation_template.html
	|--> Open File: Open the filepicker dialog window to choose a file from
	|		Google Drive to open in the editor.  Only files that have been
	|		created with the editor can be opened this way.
	|--> Save File: Save the file currently open in the editor to Google
	|		Drive.  The saved file will still contain all of the elements
	|		used by the editor to manipulate the DOM (e.g. resize handles),
	|		and so should not be loaded outside of the editor.  If a file
	|		already exists in the destination folder with the same name as
	|		that chosen to save the file under, the existing file will be
	|		overwritten.
	|--> Save As: Equivalent to 'Save File'
	|--> Publish: Export the file so it can be loaded outside of the editor.
	|		Creates a new directory inside the destination directory.  The
	|		new directory will contain the interface HTML file as well as 
	|		a directory named 'assets', in which a CSS file containing the
	|		style rules generated by the editor will be created.  All 
	|		external files needed by the interface (e.g. images, stylesheets)
	|		should be copied into the 'assets' directory before deployment.  
	|		HTML files created by the 'Publish' operation will no longer be
	|		modifiable by the editor.
	|--> Settings:
	|--> Close File: Equivalent to 'New File'

-EDIT
	|--> Copy: Copy the currently selected DOM element(s) to the clipboard
	|--> Paste: Paste the contents of the clipboard onto the working file
	|--> Undo: Undo the most recent modification to the working file
	|--> Redo: Redo the most recently undid modification to the working file
	|--> Delete Selection: Remove the currently selected DOM element(s)
	|		from the file
	|--> [Disable|Enable] Snap to Grid:  Toggle the behavior of elements
	|		being dragged.  When enabled, elements will only move in
	|		increments of 20px.  When disabled, elements will move freely.
	|		(Enabled by default)
	|--> Bring to Front: Set the currently selected element(s) as highest
	|		in the DOM stack order.
	|--> Bring forward: Set the currently selected element(s) as one level
	|		higher in the DOM stack order.
	|--> Bring backward: Set the currently selected element(s) as one level
	|		lower in the DOM stack order.
	|--> Send to Back: Set the currently selected element(s) as lowest in
			the DOM stack order.

-VIEW
	|--> Demonstrate Tutor: Load the currently opened interface in the demo
	|	window and connect to the authoring tools (behavior recorder).
	|	The authoring tools must be running locally prior to running this
	|	operation.  Also, the connection to tutordesk must not be running
	|	over HTTPS; only HTTP will allow an unsecured connection between the
	|	browser and the authoring tools.
	|--> [Show|Hide] Tab Order: Toggle whether or not the tab order (order
		in which components will gain focus when the tab key is pressed)
		is displayed in the editor.  (Hidden by default)

-INSERT
	|--> Text box: Add a text box to the interface.  Text boxes are non-
	|	interactive blocks of arbitrary text.  Double-clicking a text box
	|	will allow editing its content.
	|--> Image: Add an image to the interface.  Images can be linked via
	|	URL or loaded from Google Drive.  Images loaded from Google Drive
	|	will need to be copied into the 'assets' directory to be found by
	|	the interface after publishing.
	|--> Container: Add a container (div) element to the interface.
	|--> CTAT Component: Add a CTAT tutor component to the interface.
	|	(See 'CTAT Components' section for component descriptions)
	|--> Question Template: Add a pre-fab group of components to the
	|	interface representing a certain type of question or problem
	|--> Custom Stylesheet: Import a stylesheet from Google Drive.
		Stylesheets loaded this way will need to be copied into the
		'assets' directory to be found by the interface after publishing

