*** The Property Tool ***

The property tool is used to control the appearance and behavior of
individual components.  Its inputs are populated based on the currently
selected element.

-The 'Attributes' pane: This pane displays CTAT-specific attributes that
	can be set on the currently selected component.  See the CTAT Components
	section for descriptions of the possible attributes for each component.

-The 'Colors' pane: This pane allows you to change the foreground and
	background colors of the currently selected component.  When a text-
	based element is selected, foreground color will affect the font color.
	The 'background image' button will bring up a dialog allowing you to
	choose an image (by URL or Google Drive) to use as the background of the
	selected element.  Note that only Google Drive allows image imports; if
	you are using either of the other cloud services you will only be able
	to link images by URL.
	
-The 'Border' pane: This pane allows you to control the appearance of the
	selected element's border.  Note that both the 'width' and 'style' inputs
	must be set for the element's border to be visible.
	
-The 'Position' pane: This pane allows you to explicitly set the position of
	the selected element.  The distances are relative to the element's immediate
	parent.
	

	
	
*** CTAT Components ***	

---Attributes Common to Multiple Component Types---

-ID: Sets the "id" attribute of the selected element.  The IDs of CTAT Components
	must be unique, and can't be either of the values "done" or "hint"

-Enabled: if checked, the component will be interactive when the tutor is run

-Graded:

-Show Feedback: if checked, grading feedback will be shown on the component.

-Show Highlight: if checked, the component will be highlighted when a hint is requested
	for that step.

-Disable on Correct: if checked, the component will become non-interactive once the
	correct value has been entered.

-Font Size: Sets the font size (in px) of the component.

-Tab Order: Determines the order in which components will gain focus when the tab key
	is pressed.  Lower values will gain focus before higher values.  To display the
	tab order of all components in the interface, open the 'View' menu on the menu bar
	and click 'Show Tab Order'.  Note that this will only display tab order values that
	have been explicitly set through the Attributes pane.
	
-Label: Sets the display text on a component.

-Value (Unit Display): Sets the value for unit display components (Pie Chart and Fraction Bar).
	The value should be formatted as a summation of fractions (e.g. "1/2+1/4+(0*1/8)").
	Each fraction will constitute one 'piece' in the component.  Fractions multiplied
	by zero will be displayed as de-selected.
	
-Group Name: Sets the name of the group to which the selected component belongs.
	Components with the same group name will be graded together; for example, you can 
	use this property to denote groups of CTATRadioButtons that are part of the same problem.

---Component Descriptions---

-Text Input: A text box for single-line inputs.  Double-clicking on the element
	will allow you to edit its content.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct,
		Font Size, Tab Order.
		
	-Text Input Specific Attributes:
		Max Length: Sets the max number of characters that can be input into the component.
		
		Has Initial Focus: if checked, the component will have focus at the time the tutor
			is run.

-Text Area: A text box for multi-line inputs.  Double-clicking on the element will allow
	you to edit its content.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct,
		Font Size, Tab Order.
		
	-Text Area Specific Attributes:
		Tab on Enter: if checked, pressing the 'enter' key while the component has
			focus will be equivalent to pressing 'tab', that is, focus will switch to the
			next component in the tab order.  If not checked, pressing 'enter' will create
			a newline in the component's contents.

-Text Field: 

-Table: A grid of Text Areas.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct.
	
	-Table Specific Attributes:
		Row Count: The number of rows in the table.
		
		Column Count: The number of columns in the table.

-Pie Chart: A graphical representation of a fraction or set of fractions, in the shape
	of a circle.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct,
		Value (Unit Display).
	
	-Pie Chart Specific Attributes:
		Shadow Length: A number indicating the displacement distance of each wedge's drop shadow.
			Set to 0 to disable the drop shadows.

		Spread Distance: The number of pixels that each wedge should be displaced from the center
			of the chart. This has the effect of spacing the wedges from each other.

-Fraction Bar: A graphical representation of a fraction or set of fractions, in the shape of
	a rectangle.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct,
		Value (Unit Display).
		
	-This component has no unique attributes
	
-Number Line: A number line with customizable range and increments.

	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct.
	
	-Number Line Specific Attributes:
		Max Value: The maximum value on the number line.
		Min Value: The minimum value on the number line.
		Large Increment: The value between each large tick mark on the numberline.
			Set to '0' to disable large tick marks.
		Small Increment: The value between each small tick mark on the numberline.
			Set to '0' to disable small tick marks.
		Number of Points: The maximum number of points that can be set on the numberline.
		Point Size: The size in pixels of each point on the numberline.
		Snap to Tick Marks: If checked, points can only be set on values with corresponding
			tick marks.  If not checked, points can be set anywhere along the line.
		Angle:	The angle in degrees the numberline is rotated from the horizontal.
		
-Radio Button: A labeled radio button.  Only one radio button per group can be selected.

	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct, Label,
		Group Name.
		
	-This component has no unique attributes.
	
-Check Box: A labeled checkbox.  Any number of checkboxes per group can be selected.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct, Label.

	-This component has no unique attributes.

-Combo Box: A dropdown list of customizable options.  Options can be set through the Attribute
	Pane.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct, 
		Font Size.
	
	Combo Box Specific Attributes:
		Number of Options: Specifies the number of available options in the drop down list.
			A corresponding number of inputs will appear in the attributes pane which can
			then be used to set the values of the options themselves.
	
-DragNDrop: A container element that can be used to create sorting problems.  Typically such
	a problem will consist of two DragNDrop components which share a group name, with one
	acting as the source container and the other acting as the destination.  To populate the
	source, simply drag the components you want to be sorted onto the source container.  Use
	only non-interactive elements, such as blocks of text or images.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct,
		Group Name.
	
	-DragNDrop Specific Attributes:
		Max # of Items: Specifies the maximum number of items that can be dropped into the
			component.

-Button: A generic button element
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct, Label,
		Tab Order.
	
	-Button Specific Attributes: 
		Value (Button):  Sets the value to be used as the input of the SAI the button produces 
		when it is clicked. Default is "-1". In most cases, you will not need to change this.
		It becomes useful when using the button in conjunction with a component that has 
		data-ctat-ctrl-* attributes.

Submit Button: A button element that can be used to trigger grading on a component or group of
	components.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct, Label,
		Tab Order.
		
	-Submit Button Specific Attributes:
		Target ID: Specifies the ID of the component to trigger grading for.  Multiple components
			can be triggered by setting this to a semicolon-separated list of IDs.
		
-Audio Button: A button that can be used to play audio from the tutor.
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID, Enabled, Show Feedback, Show Highlight, Disable on Correct, Label,
		Tab Order.
	
	-Audio Button Specific Attributes:
		Source URL: Specifies the url of the audio file that clicking the button will trigger.

-Hint Widget: A grouping of three commonly-used components (Hint Window, Hint Button, and
	Done Button).
	
	-Shared Attributes: ID
	
	-Hint Widget Specific Attributes:
		Hints Enabled: If checked, users of the tutor will be able to request hints by clicking
			the hint button.
		Done Button Enabled: If checked, users will be able to signal to the tutor that they are
			done by clicking the done button.